    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/10–148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 1, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Your long delayed tels now being rec’d, last dated Sept 2 and backlog
                    apparently being transmitted chronologically. Confirm receipt all Deptels
                    through this number.</p>
                <p>Your 129 Aug 28 to Dept<note n="15" xml:id="d687fn15">Not printed.</note> and 38
                    Aug 31 to Nanking<note n="16" xml:id="d687fn16">Sent as unnumbered telegram to
                        the Department, <ref target="#pg_790">p. 790</ref>.</note> should have been
                    encoded. In future exercise caution re material transmitted plain tels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
